==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinuous
<hw>Sin"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sinuosus</ets>, fr. <ets>sinus</ets> a bent surface, a curve: cf.
F. <ets>sinueux</ets>. See <er>Sinus</er>.]</ety> <def>Bending in and
out; of a serpentine or undulating form; winding; crooked.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sin"u*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Streaking the ground with <qex>sinuous</qex> trace.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gardens bright with <qex>sinuous</qex> rills.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinupalliate</ent>⟦br⟧
